                                                                                               NIST SP 800-161r1                                 CYBERSECURITY SUPPLY CHAIN RISK MANAGEMENT
                                                                                                                                                    PRACTICES FOR SYSTEMS AND ORGANIZATIONS


                                                                                                Term                         Definition
                                                                                                risk response                Intentional and informed decision and actions to accept, avoid,
                                                                                                [NIST SP 800-53 Rev. 5,      mitigate, share, or transfer an identified risk.
                                                                                                adapted]
                                                                                                risk response plan           A summary of potential consequence(s) of the successful
                                                                                                                             exploitation of a specific vulnerability or vulnerabilities by a
                                                                                                                             threat agent, as well as mitigating strategies and C-SCRM
                                                                                                                             controls.
                                                                                                risk tolerance               The organization’s or stakeholder’s readiness to bear the
This publication is available free of charge from: https://doi.org/10.6028/NIST.SP.800-161r1




                                                                                                [NIST 8286, adapted]         remaining risk after responding to or considering the risk in
                                                                                                                             order to achieve its objectives.
                                                                                                secondary market             An unofficial, unauthorized, or unintended distribution
                                                                                                                             channel.
                                                                                                security control             The safeguards or countermeasures prescribed for an
                                                                                                [NIST SP 800-53 Rev. 5]      information system or an organization to protect the
                                                                                                                             confidentiality, integrity, and availability of the system and its
                                                                                                                             information.
                                                                                                software bill of materials   A formal record containing the details and supply chain
                                                                                                Exec. Order No. 14028,       relationships of various components used in building software.
                                                                                                supra note 1, § 10(j)        Software developers and vendors often create products by
                                                                                                                             assembling existing open source and commercial software
                                                                                                                             components. The SBOM enumerates these components in a
                                                                                                                             product.

                                                                                                supplier                     Organization or individual that enters into an agreement with
                                                                                                [ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,         the acquirer or integrator for the supply of a product or service.
                                                                                                adapted]                     This includes all suppliers in the supply chain, developers or
                                                                                                [NIST SP 800-53 Rev. 5,      manufacturers of systems, system components, or system
                                                                                                adapted from definition of   services; systems integrators; suppliers; product resellers; and
                                                                                                “developer”]                 third-party partners.

                                                                                                supply chain                 Linked set of resources and processes between and among
                                                                                                [ISO 28001, adapted]         multiple levels of organizations, each of which is an acquirer,
                                                                                                                             that begins with the sourcing of products and services and
                                                                                                                             extends through their life cycle.
                                                                                                supply chain element         Organizations, entities, or tools employed for the research and
                                                                                                                             development, design, manufacturing, acquisition, delivery,
                                                                                                                             integration, operations and maintenance, and/or disposal of
                                                                                                                             systems and system components.




